    "body": "> We need root privileges to create the shared data directory (in `/Library/Application Support`) on OSX, which means completely redoing our packaging there.  That's too big a job for the next release, so removing from the milestone.\r\n\r\nActually, this is quite straightforward.  On OSX we can prompt the user on first run with a dialog asking them if they want to configure OpenRA for all users on the system (&rarr; password dialog + create `/Library/Application Support/OpenRA`), or just for themselves (do nothing - same behaviour as now)."
